{"_id":"S1cc29KoX","title":"Reference in c++","body":{"entityMap":{},"blocks":[{"key":"ag6qs","text":"Reference in c++","type":"header-one","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"25dho","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fq77n","text":"#include <iostream>\n\nusing namespace std;\n\nvoid bat(int a[],int &i){\n    i++;\n    i++;\n    cout<<\"this is i \"<<i<<endl;\n    cout<<a[i]<<endl;\n    \n}\n\n\nint main()\n{\n    int a[] = {1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8};\n    int index = 0;\n    bat(a,index);\n\n    return 0;\n}\n","type":"custom-code-block-cpp","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"59kd9","text":"the output of this is ","type":"header-two","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4c60g","text":"this is i 2                                                                                                                                                                            \n3","type":"custom-code-block-cpp","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8hj6k","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"b6302","text":"here \" i \" is the reference to 0 index, when we add 1 to it , it becomes reference to the 1 index, But suppose we pass direct value to \"bat\" function it will show error eg:-- ","type":"header-two","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4jl74","text":"bat(a,0);","type":"custom-code-block-cpp","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8u2u9","text":"This will show an error.","type":"header-two","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}]},"dateCreated":"2018-10-21T06:28:34.048Z","lastUpdated":"2018-10-21T06:35:00.334Z"}
